I loved the movie ! Saw it last night BUT I have one major issue with it. And its not specific to this...
body:
SHAZAM !

Post movie thoughts.

I loved the movie ! Saw it last night BUT I have one major issue with it. And its not specific to this movie.

So obviously ahead…

Ok so in this movie there was a pretty long fight scene of them flying and its just not that good, I loved this movie but in the finale there were 2 fight scenes happening at once it cut from Billys flight fight and a carnival fight. Id rather just see the carnival one evertime it cut back to Billy I was so dissapointed. In anymovie that does this they fuck it up it just looks so fake.

I expected this !

And got this

Only example I can think of thats live action movie doing this right is Man Of Steel

And no other movie seems to be able to do this right at all fighting and flying seems so simple tho I mean just copy Dragon ball Z !

summary:
Carol Danvers x Reader
I was really bored so I wrote some headcanons on how carol’s first pride would look...
body:
Carol’s first pride headcanons

Carol Danvers x Reader

I was really bored so I wrote some headcanons on how carol’s first pride would look like

_______________________________________________

- You asking her whether she wanted to go to pride with you sometime in spring

- Her obviously agreeing

- You telling her about all the new developments concerning the lgbtq+ community

- She’s really happy that a lot of things have seemed to changed though she knows there’s still a lot of things to be done

- Starting to prepare when june comes around

- Ordering a bunch of flags, stickers and shirts

- Her becoming more and more excited about the prospect of going to such an event

- When the day finally arrives, she’s up even earlier than usual and bouncing around the apartment all enthusiastically and ready to party

- You drawing two lesbian flags on her cheeks and drawing (your sexuality) flags on yours

- Tying pride flags around your necks, like capes

 - You two basically going all out in terms of accessories

- Getting to the parade really early to get the best spots

- Thor, being the great ally that he is, joining you two

- All the other avengers making a surprise appearance to show their support

- Carol being really fascinated by all the different kinds of people, sexualities and identities, she just basically wants to befriend everyone

- Ending up in a pride group chat with 50+ people, being invited to an after-pride party the next weekend

- You’ve never seen carol so happy and free before

- Her telling you how much she loves you at least 20 times

- She usually isn’t a huge fan of pda, but she’s making an exception because she feels safe

- When she notices the homophobic preachers though, she sees red

- Her almost punching each and everyone in the face so you had to hold her back, which you’ve barely managed to do

- Her being a bit sad after that but you pulled her out of it rather quickly with lots of kisses and cuddles

- Being her usual bubbly self after about 5 minutes and befriending various more people

- Deciding to go to a gay bar in the evening

- A lot of dancing and kissing (duh)

- When you got home, she couldn’t stop smiling

- Her thanking you for taking her and making you promise to go again next year

_______________________________________________

Quick disclaimer: English is not my first language, if you haven’t noticed, so please excuse any mistakes

Tell me what you think😊

summary: Okay okay
body:
Okay okay

So,

We’ve all seen some stupid reviews of men being pissed at the captain marvel movie for some dumb reason or the other yeah?

I was reading through some comment pre-workout to get some angry energy to fuel myself and then I read a comment, which i shit you not says something along the lines of

“They showed fury washing dishes when they could have easily shown carol, who was in the kitchen, washing the dishes. This is clearly some bullshit propaganda they’re pushing on us”

Which, you’re kidding right? You’re angry that a very capable man was…. washing dishes? Gee bro dk how pompously entitled and sexist you have to be to make that comment but in any case go on, please tell us more of your complaints as the stack if dirty dishes in your sink continues to grow.

Oh and ps i dont know what other people do but in my culture it is pretty normalised to offer to clean up after your host serves you, so like :/
